You are working on rts-agent, a multiplayer agent orchestration platform with an RTS-style top-down view.

STACK: React 18 + Vite + Three.js (R3F) + Tailwind v4 + Convex (reactive DB, no WebSocket). No custom WS code.

READ THESE FILES FIRST on every task:
- ARCHITECTURE.md — Convex schema, data flow, component responsibilities
- UI.md — layout spec, visual states, workflows, animation budget
- PLAN.md — hour-by-hour build order
- client/src/lib/types.ts — AgentView, AgentStatus, RoomMap
- client/src/lib/characters.ts — Character type, CHARACTERS array
- convex/schema.ts — the DB schema (source of truth for all data shapes)

I am Person 1 (Frontend). I own /client/**. My partner owns /convex/** and /agent-runner/**.

DESIGN DIRECTION — this is critical:
- Dark background (stone-950 base), rich saturated accent colors — NOT monochrome
- Each agent character has a distinct color (teal, yellow, red, purple, green) — use these aggressively
- Vibe: developer tool meets RTS game. Think Warp terminal + StarCraft command UI
- Animations must feel premium, not childish. Smooth spring physics, subtle glows, clean easing
- Use Tailwind v4 classes. No CSS modules. Font is system sans-serif
- R3F for the game world, HTML/Tailwind for all HUD panels
- Convex for all data: useQuery for reads, useMutation for writes. No local mock data.
